# ============================================================================
#  .gitignore for the IFRS 9 ECL Framework
#
#  THE GOLDEN RULE: the live dashboard only needs the small JSON files in
#  models/. It NEVER needs the raw loan data, the feature store, or the
#  database. Those are gigabytes and GitHub rejects files over 100 MB, so we
#  exclude the entire data/ folder. config/settings.py recreates the empty
#  data folders automatically when the app starts, so nothing breaks.
# ============================================================================

# ---- Large data: NEVER commit (raw Fannie Mae loans, parquet, feature store)
data/

# ---- Secrets: NEVER commit (DB password, FRED API key live here)
.env
*.env

# ---- Python noise ----
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*.egg-info/
.pytest_cache/
.ipynb_checkpoints/

# ---- Virtual environments ----
.venv/
venv/
env/
ENV/

# ---- Database dumps ----
*.db
*.sqlite
*.sql
*.dump

# ---- Generated reports & logs (HTML + parquet exports, regenerated by pipeline) ----
reports/
logs/
*.log

# ---- OS / editor noise ----
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
.vscode/
.idea/

# ============================================================================
#  WHAT *IS* COMMITTED (so the website works):
#    - all source code (src/, config/, tests/)
#    - config/config.yaml  (paths + thresholds, no secrets)
#    - models/*.json        (the data the dashboard reads — KEEP THESE)
#    - models/*.joblib      (small trained models, ~4 MB total — fine to keep)
#    - requirements.txt, README.md, .gitignore
# ============================================================================